To Download rdkb-2.1-20161205 
$ mkdir rpi-rdkb
$ cd rpi-rdkb
$ repo init -u https://code.rdkcentral.com/r/manifests -m rdkb.xml -b rdkb-2.1-20161205
$ repo sync -j4 --no-clone-bundle

In rdkb-2.1-20161205 (latest stable revision), there is no BSP layers to support Raspberrypi.
So Copying the BSP layer from the Krogoth Branch.

BSP Layer to be copied:meta-cmf-raspberrypi

Source Command : source meta-cmf-raspberrypi/setup-environment

Copy meta-openembedded/meta-python to rpi-rdkb/meta-openembedded/

Copy meta-openembedded/meta-oe/recipes-devtools/cunit to rpi-rdkb/meta-openembedded/meta-oe/recipes-devtools/

Copy openembedded-core/meta/classes/remove-libtool.bbclass to rpi-rdkb/openembedded-core/meta/classes

In meta-cmf-raspberrypi layer,rename dbus_%.bbappend file. ( ./meta-cmf-raspberrypi/recipes-core/dbus/dbus_%.bbappendold so that, bitbake will not consider)

Add init-ifupdown and initscripts packages in 
meta-cmf-raspberrypi/recipes-core/packagegroups/packagegroup-rdk-oss-broadband.bbappend file.

The other packages needed from krogoth branch are:

hostapd version 2.5
path- meta-openembedded/meta-oe/recipes-connectivity/

busybox version 1.24.1
path- openembedded-core/meta/recipes-core/

dnsmasq version 2.75
path- meta-openembedded/meta-networking/recipes-support/

Bitbake Image  : bitbake rdk-generic-broadband-image
